    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct — ASTM F1717 static loading only",
      "description": "Assessment is applicable exclusively to the non-cannulated 7.5 mm titanium-alloy pedicle screw construct tested under ASTM F1717 quasi-static compression-bending at room temperature (22 ± 2 °C). Cannulated variants, dynamic fatigue loading, in vivo bone-implant interface conditions, and constructs outside the 40–60 mm interbody spacer height range are explicitly excluded from this COU."
    },
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "ASTM F1717 quasi-static compression-bending operating envelope",
      "description": "Displacement-controlled quasi-static loading at 5 mm/min crosshead speed; applied bending moment 0–200 N·m; axial compressive preload 100 ± 5 N; construct rod diameter 5.5 mm CoCr; screw outer diameter 7.5 ± 0.05 mm; interbody spacer height 45 mm nominal; ambient temperature 22 ± 2 °C; relative humidity 40–60%; test machine compliance <0.5 μm/N. FEA boundary conditions replicate fixture geometry within ±0.2 mm tolerance."
    }
  },
